{t: Heart and Soul}
{st: (Frank Loesser/Hoagy Carmichael), 1938; many performers}

{textcolour: blue}
[Intro]
[C] Heart and [Am] soul, I [F] begged to [G] be adored,
[C] Lost con- [Am] trol, [F] and tumbled [G] overboard,
[C] Gladly... [Am] [F]
That magic [G] night [C] we kissed, [Am]
